18 meirt
Amst Rover
op 15 deser was aen ue mijnen laesten tsedert verstaen, dat het
convoy van costij 6 deser van hul was vertrocken, & alhoewelick
geen advis hebbe het selve gearriveert te syn, soo verhope geen
ongemack sak sijn overgekomen, maer morgen hun arrivement te
vernemen, den brief van 114 £100: van 4eorge tliffort getrocke
p Janis laest ten laste Jan & fran Eyler in londen den
welcken, om het bewast abus, is geprotesteert faute van acceptatie
& op ue goetvinden andermael gerenvoyeert, alsoo den selven behorlyck
soude worden betaelt met de incosten, soo seynde ue hier ingesloten te
rugge met het protest van non acceptatie, & een protest faute van betaling
alsoo die acceptanten hebben geweygert te betaelen, de 4 ƒ & 6 utt
voor oncosten dae comme geresen, ingevolge ue mij ka de geloft
soude geschieden, & oock meer danreden is, destemeer, omdat de
faute bij den trecker selfs is begaen, derhalven gelieft het capitael
beneffens d'oncosten intevoorden volgens aenden voet deser, dogh soo mij
lufford tegende provisie van ½ ps iedt wilde seggen, moet hy weten
te londen sulckx costume is, alhoewel hier & costij beter coop wort gedaen
dogh alsoo ick niet wille sicaneren, soo ben tevreden met wat ue daer inne
sal doen, dan andermael dat gelt tot londen te ontfangen is present mijne con
venientie niet. ingesloten een anderbrief van st ƒ 200:- a 33: 2 en tot
laste I saae Clifford, den welcken gelieft te laeten accepteren & my teragge
seynde hope ditto Clifford eeh suffisant man is, dat geirne verneme
Londen n Kent
18 meirt
My last to you was 15 curt to which referre you, & accordingley
exspect some spa clothes by the first departinge convoy, which I suppose
that for amst & should be gladiif a sppe fine or two new culloure
were by, now have before mee yours of 27 past, where by take notice
hew you father could lind no cure for his disease & that he was
up the day before he dead pray advise, if he in a sudden
sby a fitl, or that he was by sheis witt & speach, tillhes dyinge
& whether he did not decline instrenght ayes & sto macke, some
time, of monthe ofweecks before, that so you did like forsee his
approtfachinge devange, praij s lett mee have a particular acctt
there of, the ships from hull are not yett arrived,
neither anney news of them, god send them safe, as
to the 12 northreus mr no modish to be found
to content lett one or 2 blew grayes bee, if to be had
which I suppose to bee, because there is blew grayps
here in towe in northrens, therefore lett mee have
1 a 2 bleuw grayes of 5 clothes & leave out other mo
dish because doo not so nmuch want them, as well
the grayes. itt zeems the coffie cullour will come in some
demande in low prises, therefore ad a 6p more from
7 to 10 some what leighter sonme
then the patt of 25 cur & if you have sent mee
29 pack with tohe amst convoy, & that the convoy for
mott lailes before anney for ostend, so send some spa
clothes also that way, that by so odoeinge, I can have the
goods before a convoij sailes fbre ostend, & if non readdy
